<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <style>
      body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; }
      .container { max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }
      .header { background-color: #343a40; color: white; padding: 20px; text-align: center; }
      .content { padding: 30px 20px; background-color: #f8f9fa; }
      .credentials { background-color: #e9ecef; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 20px 0; }
      .footer { padding: 20px; text-align: center; color: #666; font-size: 12px; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="header">
        <h1>New User Created</h1>
        <p>Admin Notification</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="content">
        <p><strong>Hi Jamie,</strong></p>
        
        <p>A new user has been successfully created in the Bravik system:</p>

        <div class="credentials">
          <h3>User Details</h3>
          <p><strong>Name:</strong> <%= @user.first_name %> <%= @user.last_name %></p>
          <p><strong>Email:</strong> <%= @user.email %></p>
          <p><strong>Role:</strong> <%= @user.role %></p>
          <p><strong>Plan:</strong> <%= @user.plan_name %></p>
          <p><strong>Temporary Password:</strong> <%= @temp_password %></p>
        </div>
        
        <p>The user account has been set up with:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Stripe customer account</li>
          <li>Pinecone assistant</li>
          <li>Initial query allocation</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>Next Steps:</strong></p>
        <p>Once the user has paid their setup invoice, use the admin dashboard to send them their login credentials.</p>
        
        <p>Login URL for reference: <a href="<%= @login_url %>"><%= @login_url %></a></p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="footer">
        <p>This is an automated notification from the Bravik admin system.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>